OL,3,CThe radical water fix: New regulator,
OL,4,Ccompulsory meters and higher bills
OL,6,FA new water ombudsman would give
OL,7,F"stronger protection to customers and
OL,8,Fa clearer route to resolving
OL,9,Fcomplaints."
OL,11,FThe existing water network is in such
OL,12,Fa state of decrepitude that vast sums
OL,13,Fof money will be needed just to
OL,14,Fupgrade and maintain it.
OL,16,FWater bills will rise significantly.
OL,18,FCunliffe recommends the introduction
OL,19,Fof a National Social Tariff to protect
OL,20,Fvulnerable households.
