OL,3,CThe radical water fix: New regulator,
OL,4,Ccompulsory meters and higher bills
OL,6,FThe current voluntary system is
OL,7,Finadequate, capping the annual bill
OL,8,Ffor a single parent on a low income at
OL,9,F#91 in Portsmouth, but #364 in
OL,10,FBradford.
OL,12,FHe also backs compulsory water
OL,13,Fmetering - a change likely to prove
OL,14,Funpopular with larger families or
OL,15,Fthose living in big homes in rural
OL,16,Fareas.
OL,18,FThe new regulator is intended to be
OL,19,Fmore effective than Ofwat, with
OL,20,Fgreater powers to keep water companies
OL,21,Fon the straight and narrow.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
