OL,3,CThe radical water fix: New regulator,
OL,4,Ccompulsory meters and higher bills
OL,6,FHe was free to recommend whatever
OL,7,Fsolutions he judged necessary - apart
OL,8,Ffrom nationalisation, which the
OL,9,Fgovernment ruled out.
OL,11,FCunliffe says he wouldn't have
OL,12,Frecommended state control anyway.
OL,14,FWhile acknowledging well-publicised
OL,15,Fand unacceptable failures, he believes
OL,16,Fthe privatisation of the water
OL,17,Findustry in 1989 has also delivered
OL,18,Freal achievements ` too easily
OL,19,Fforgotten, he says.
